                        <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-900">How much should I tip my tattoo artist?</h3>
                        <i class="fas fa-chevron-down text-purple-600 transition-transform duration-300"></i>
                    </button>
                    <div class="mt-2 text-gray-600 hidden">
                        <p>The standard tip is 15-20% of the total cost, similar to restaurant tipping. For larger pieces, you might tip per session. If you're on a tight budget, even a smaller tip with a heartfelt thank you is appreciated.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- FAQ Item 4 -->
                <div class="mb-6 border-b border-gray-200 pb-6">
                    <button class="flex justify-between items-center w-full text-left focus:outline-none">
                        <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-900">Can I negotiate the price with a tattoo artist?</h3>
                        <i class="fas fa-chevron-down text-purple-600 transition-transform duration-300"></i>
                    </button>
                    <div class="mt-2 text-gray-600 hidden">
                        <p>Generally no - tattoo pricing reflects the artist's skill, experience, and time. However, you can discuss options like simplifying the design or breaking a large piece into multiple sessions to fit your budget. Never try to underpay for quality work.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
